  <testcase name="document_transactional_silent_no_op_scenarios" classname="com.techleadguru.phase2.day28.Day28PrivateMethodTransactionalTest" time="0.004">
    <system-out><![CDATA[[DAY 28] @Transactional SILENT NO-OP SCENARIOS:

  1. Private method:
     @Transactional private void myMethod() { ... }
     CGLIB cannot override private methods → advice never fires.
     FIX: Make method public OR extract to separate @Service bean.

  2. Not a Spring bean:
     new OrderService(repo).placeOrder()
     No proxy exists → @Transactional decorative only.
     FIX: Always inject via @Autowired / constructor injection.

  3. Self-invocation:
     this.placeOrder() inside the same class.
     Bypasses proxy → @Transactional ignored.
     FIX: Extract to separate @Service OR AopContext.currentProxy().

  RULE: @Transactional only works on PUBLIC methods of Spring-managed beans
        called via the Spring proxy (not via 'this').
]]></system-out>
  </testcase>
